1
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:41,560
Tang Yan

2
00:00:46,479 --> 00:00:47,679
Ying Tang, why are you here?

3
00:00:47,759 --> 00:00:48,759
Don't you have class today?

4
00:00:48,799 --> 00:00:49,640
I missed the preliminary entrance exam.

5
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:51,039
I can't take the Gaokao anymore.

6
00:00:51,119 --> 00:00:52,000
It's all your fault.

7
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,600
It doesn't matter.

8
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,439
It's just the Gaokao.

9
00:00:55,439 --> 00:00:56,359
You still say it doesn't matter?

10
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:57,200
Look here.

11
00:00:57,759 --> 00:00:59,280
My dad has such a big factory.

12
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:02,240
After I marry you,

13
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:04,359
you won't have to work hard to earn money.

14
00:01:04,359 --> 00:01:05,120
Right?

15
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,480
Come on now.

16
00:01:09,799 --> 00:01:10,400
Really.

17
00:01:11,319 --> 00:01:11,840
How do I treat you?

18
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,079
You know very well.

19
00:01:14,519 --> 00:01:15,560
I still have things to do here.

20
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,159
I'm leaving now.

21
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,359
I don't have class today.

22
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,079
I can stay with you.

23
00:01:23,359 --> 00:01:24,879
I have business to handle.

24
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:25,799
I'm busy.

25
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,640
Be good, go back first.

26
00:01:28,159 --> 00:01:29,000
No.

27
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:31,159
I finally got a free day today.

28
00:01:31,319 --> 00:01:32,040
Stop crying.

29
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,040
Ying Tang.

30
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:35,319
Ying Tang.

31
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:36,400
It really is you.

32
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,040
You...

33
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:38,920
You're dating someone?

34
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,040
Who the hell are you?

35
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,400
What business do you have with my woman?

36
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,120
Ying Tang.

37
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:47,280
Just give me a little more time.

38
00:01:47,439 --> 00:01:48,879
I'll definitely be able to buy a house in the city.

39
00:01:51,040 --> 00:01:51,959
Are you stupid?

40
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,040
Those are all excuses.

41
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:56,159
I'm dating Tang Yan now.

42
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:58,079
I can have whatever I want.

43
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,200
Ying Tang.

44
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,359
Who is this guy?

45
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,760
He's just a poor neighbor.

46
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,760
Let's ignore him.

47
00:02:06,439 --> 00:02:07,319
Poor neighbor.

48
00:02:09,159 --> 00:02:09,840
Why don't you take a look

49
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,120
at your own pathetic self?

50
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,840
Telling my woman what to do.

51
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,039
Get lost.

52
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:18,560
Tang Yan!

53
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:19,879
Who is she?

54
00:02:26,159 --> 00:02:27,039
Sister-in-law.

55
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,039
Sister-in-law.

56
00:02:28,639 --> 00:02:29,360
Zheng Xiaochuan.

57
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,840
I'll deal with the Zheng family business later.

58
00:02:32,039 --> 00:02:32,800
Move out of my way.

59
00:02:33,039 --> 00:02:33,840
Move!

60
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:36,159
I'm going to beat this bitch who stole my man to death!

61
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:36,759
Sister-in-law, calm down!

62
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:37,879
Who stole your man?

63
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:39,439
Who is your man?

64
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:40,400
I'll beat you to death!

65
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,759
You stole my man!

66
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:42,560
Who are you?

67
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,319
Let go of me!

68
00:02:43,319 --> 00:02:44,240
Stand right there!

69
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:47,439
Ask him!

70
00:02:47,439 --> 00:02:48,520
Who is his girlfriend?

71
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:49,360
Who is your girlfriend?

72
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:49,759
Psycho.

73
00:02:49,759 --> 00:02:50,599
Explain it clearly to me.

74
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:51,919
Am I your woman,

75
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:52,960
or is she your woman?

76
00:02:53,159 --> 00:02:54,199
I... I don't know!

77
00:02:54,319 --> 00:02:54,719
Speak up!

78
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:55,879
Did you seduce my man?

79
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:56,759
You're the seducer!

80
00:02:56,919 --> 00:02:57,759
Seeing the way you look,

81
00:02:57,759 --> 00:02:58,120
makes me want to hit you!

82
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,280
Have you no shame?

83
00:02:59,280 --> 00:02:59,960
I don't know!

84
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:00,719
You shut up!

85
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,680
You're the shameless one!

86
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,520
Wang Yingtang.

87
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,719
Why are you here?

88
00:03:10,479 --> 00:03:11,719
Mom, I don't have a boyfriend.

89
00:03:11,759 --> 00:03:12,680
I really don't.

90
00:03:13,479 --> 00:03:14,800
You and Yang Liu were at the factory gate.

91
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:15,639
And got into a fight.

92
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:16,479
What happened?

93
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,280
You became a mistress and are too ashamed to admit it?

94
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,240
Is that how a sister should speak?

95
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,879
Mistress this, mistress that.

96
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:24,919
If word of this gets out,

97
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:27,479
do you want your sister to die?

98
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:28,680
Yang Liu was cursing so nastily,

99
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,479
and you couldn't even stop her.

100
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,520
You let your sister become a laughingstock.

101
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,360
Alright, alright.

102
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:33,039
Mom.

103
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,199
It's all because of you.

104
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:35,120
That's right, Mom.

105
00:03:35,479 --> 00:03:36,400
Look at Second Sister.

106
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:37,759
She made me fail to get into college.

107
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,159
And now she's ruining my reputation.

108
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,120
What she owes me,

109
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,680
she can't pay back in this lifetime.

110
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,840
Mom.

111
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:47,000
What does that have to do with Second Sister?

112
00:03:47,319 --> 00:03:49,039
Both are my own flesh and blood.

113
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,199
Isn't Second Sister your daughter too?

114
00:03:51,759 --> 00:03:52,639
Ruined.

115
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:53,560
This family...

116
00:03:53,719 --> 00:03:56,039
has been ruined by this ignorant girl.

117
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,080
Brother.

118
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:14,759
I want to tell you something.

119
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,560
Go ahead.

120
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:17,600
I saw Sister-in-law today.

121
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:18,920
She's back.

122
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:21,160
I know.

123
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:22,920
You've met?

124
00:04:23,959 --> 00:04:24,360
Then...

125
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,000
should we tell Mom about this?

126
00:04:26,959 --> 00:04:28,240
I'm not with her anymore.

127
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:29,800
No need to tell Mom.

128
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:30,959
Alright.

129
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:32,399
Brother.

130
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:33,360
Then...

131
00:04:33,959 --> 00:04:35,720
then promise me one thing too.

132
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:38,240
What is it?

133
00:04:42,759 --> 00:04:44,279
I want to make vinegar with Sister Yingrong.

134
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:47,759
This...

135
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,600
what does this have to do with the Vinegar Workshop?

136
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:51,920
I want to earn money.

137
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,920
I don't want to be looked down on anymore.

138
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,360
I don't want to be called poor and pathetic.

139
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,120
And I don't want to be seen as a loser.

140
00:05:00,959 --> 00:05:01,959
What set you off?

141
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:03,839
Anyway, whether you agree or not,

142
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,160
I'm joining the Vinegar Workshop.

143
00:05:06,079 --> 00:05:07,319
I'm all grown up now.

144
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,720
I want to earn my own money.

145
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:10,199
I want to earn lots and lots of money.

146
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:30,800
With the late 1980s,

147
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,240
the state gradually clarified the private economy,

148
00:05:33,920 --> 00:05:37,160
and policies encouraging entrepreneurship swept through.

149
00:05:37,439 --> 00:05:40,079
Zheng Haiyang and Zheng Xiaochuan,

150
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:42,079
under the leadership of Wang Yingrong,

151
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:45,360
threw themselves into the vinegar business.

152
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,839
Their path grew wider,

153
00:05:48,199 --> 00:05:51,279
and the future looked bright.

154
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,439
Let's go.

155
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:38,759
So,

156
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,759
all this time,

157
00:06:41,439 --> 00:06:43,519
you just came up with a few half-finished products?

158
00:06:43,959 --> 00:06:45,279
What half-finished products?

159
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:47,560
Those are the new products we researched.

160
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,319
Just taste it.

161
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,720
Me?

162
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,759
Why don't you taste it?

163
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,160
Using me as a guinea pig?

164
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:02,879
Big Brother is just chicken.

165
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,759
Exactly.

166
00:07:05,079 --> 00:07:05,920
Look at what you're saying.

167
00:07:06,319 --> 00:07:07,000
What do you mean chicken?

168
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:10,800
I told you not to ask him to come.

169
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,040
Scared off by a little vinegar.

170
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:14,480
Forget it.

171
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:15,680
Forget it, forget it.

172
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,399
Can't count on him.

173
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:17,279
Drink it yourself.

174
00:07:17,279 --> 00:07:18,399
Forget it, Big Brother just doesn't dare.

175
00:07:19,519 --> 00:07:20,560
Me, scared off?

176
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:22,120
Even if it sets my teeth on edge today,

177
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:23,160
I'm going to drink it.

178
00:07:33,079 --> 00:07:33,759
What are you looking at?

179
00:07:57,079 --> 00:07:57,720
How is it?

180
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,680
Is it sour with a hint of sweetness?

181
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,120
Try this.

182
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:09,279
How is this one?

183
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,279
Right, right.

184
00:08:10,439 --> 00:08:11,199
Drink, drink.

185
00:08:11,519 --> 00:08:11,920
This one.

186
00:08:12,399 --> 00:08:12,920
Try this one again.

187
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,519
This one should be closer.

188
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,040
And this one, and this one.

189
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:16,839
And this one, and this one.

190
00:08:16,839 --> 00:08:17,079
Drink.

191
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:17,519
This one.

192
00:08:17,519 --> 00:08:17,759
Drink.

193
00:08:18,279 --> 00:08:18,519
Drink.

194
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,000
You...

195
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:26,920
This stuff...

196
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:30,319
isn't vinegar.

197
00:08:30,879 --> 00:08:31,839
It's wine!

198
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,120
That's impossible.

199
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,240
Let me smell it.

200
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:38,799
Ying...

201
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,159
Sister Yingrong.

202
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,480
That really smells like wine.

203
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,840
Maybe...

204
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:44,799
the vinegar mash went wrong.

205
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:51,559
This...

206
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,399
It's not the vinegar mash.

207
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:56,360
The ratios are all correct.

208
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,120
Brother.

209
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,039
Stop drinking.

210
00:09:02,039 --> 00:09:03,120
I actually think...

211
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:03,919
this...

212
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,519
this tastes pretty good.

213
00:09:06,559 --> 00:09:08,639
It's all good, all tasty.

214
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,639
Stop drinking, stop drinking.

215
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,200
Drink! Let's drink together!

216
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,039
Okay, okay, okay.

217
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:14,759
Okay, okay, okay.

218
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:16,320
Brother.

219
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:18,519
Darn it, darn it.

220
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,320
We're done for.

221
00:09:31,519 --> 00:09:32,519
You drank so much.

222
00:09:32,519 --> 00:09:34,039
This liquor is pretty strong.

223
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,159
Li Guangming.

224
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,240
You think you can hide?

225
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:44,600
I wasn't hiding, Mr. Tang.

226
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:45,679
Those few days...

227
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,600
I went to find skilled workers.

228
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:48,960
But they said it's imported.

229
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,600
Never seen it before.

230
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,000
Can't fix it.

231
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,399
Can't fix it?

232
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:55,679
My factory took a 500,000 order.

233
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,639
And now you tell me it can't be fixed.

234
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:58,759
Fine.

235
00:09:59,200 --> 00:09:59,879
If you can't fix it...

236
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:00,919
Then I will...

237
00:10:00,919 --> 00:10:01,799
send you to the police station.

238
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:03,399
Mr. Tang, Mr. Tang, Mr. Tang.

239
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,559
Give me a little more time.

240
00:10:04,759 --> 00:10:05,279
Just a little more.

241
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:07,519
I'll find my cousin, Director Wu.

242
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:09,559
Ask him to bring in some outside experts.

243
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:10,600
Still waiting?

244
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,360
I told you to get Engineer Zheng.

245
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,320
Where is he?

246
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,759
I... I looked for him.

247
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:15,840
He...

248
00:10:16,679 --> 00:10:18,080
He said he can't fix it.

249
00:10:19,279 --> 00:10:20,720
The villagers all say he can.

250
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,559
How could he not be able to fix it?

251
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:24,200
Did you not explain the payment...

252
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,120
clearly to him?

253
00:10:25,159 --> 00:10:25,759
No...

254
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,840
I did say it.

255
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:27,799
Dad.

256
00:10:28,559 --> 00:10:30,559
I also invited this guy named Zheng.

257
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:33,279
He admitted his skills aren't good enough.

258
00:10:34,159 --> 00:10:35,679
And I even offered him a raise.

259
00:10:36,559 --> 00:10:37,639
He didn't dare accept it.

260
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:40,799
Plus, that guy has a really bad temper.

261
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:41,679
He even hits people.

262
00:10:41,679 --> 00:10:43,120
Shut your mouth.

263
00:10:43,759 --> 00:10:45,120
With that rotten temper of yours...

264
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:47,120
you have the nerve to talk about others?

265
00:10:48,159 --> 00:10:48,879
Did you...

266
00:10:48,879 --> 00:10:50,279
talk rudely to him again...

267
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,600
and make Engineer Zheng angry?

268
00:10:51,759 --> 00:10:52,840
No.

269
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,360
Right now, this factory...

270
00:10:55,799 --> 00:10:57,120
can't keep running.

271
00:10:57,879 --> 00:10:58,919
I'm telling you two...

272
00:10:59,399 --> 00:11:00,679
no matter what method you use...

273
00:11:00,879 --> 00:11:03,080
I must see Engineer Zheng today.

274
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:03,879
Understood.

275
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:04,519
Understood.

276
00:11:04,879 --> 00:11:05,399
Then...

277
00:11:05,759 --> 00:11:07,240
let's invite him again.

278
00:11:07,879 --> 00:11:08,519
Let's go.

279
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:11,120
Hurry up.

280
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,519
I know.

281
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:18,720
Stop pushing me.

282
00:11:18,799 --> 00:11:19,279
Go.

283
00:11:22,039 --> 00:11:23,559
Which of you will take your brother back?

284
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:25,159
I'll come over after I finish the vinegar mash.

285
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,919
This time was a mistake.

286
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:45,559
I really learned from my Second Aunt.

287
00:11:45,919 --> 00:11:47,399
I have talent, too.

288
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:50,600
Right.

289
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:55,720
You be careful.

290
00:12:08,559 --> 00:12:09,799
What are you looking at?

291
00:12:10,759 --> 00:12:11,840
If you keep looking...

